@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api
@studentToken = ...
@mentorToken = ...

### ------------------------------------------------------------------------
### MY MENTOR (STUDENT & MENTOR)
### ------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Request Mentoring Session (Student)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mentoring-sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "mentor_id": 2, 
    "type": "academic",
    "schedule": "2025-12-01 10:00:00"
}

### List My Sessions (Student)
GET {{baseUrl}}/my-mentoring-sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Accept: application/json

### Update Session Status (Mentor)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mentoring-sessions/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{mentorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "status": "scheduled"
}

### Submit Need Assessment (Student - Pre-mentoring)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mentoring-sessions/1/need-assessments
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "form_data": {
        "learning_goals": "Improve architecture skills",
        "previous_experience": "Built 2 apps",
        "challenges": "Scaling",
        "expectations": "Code review"
    }
}

### Upload Coaching File (Mentor)
# Note: In VS Code REST Client, file uploads are tricky. 
# This is a simulation of the endpoint structure.
POST {{baseUrl}}/mentoring-sessions/1/coaching-files
Authorization: Bearer {{mentorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "file_name": "Roadmap.pdf",
    "file_type": "pdf",
    "uploaded_by": 2
    // "file": (binary data)
}

### List Coaching Files (Student)
GET {{baseUrl}}/mentoring-sessions/1/coaching-files
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Accept: application/json
